    "department": "Revenue",
    "description": "About Cryptio\n\nWe’re Cryptio. We build infrastructure to bring financial integrity to the crypto economy. Our enterprise-grade back-office and data platform power mission-critical accounting, reporting, and operational workflows for institutions, corporates, and crypto-native organisations.\n\nWe’re trusted by leaders like Circle, Societe Generale, Uniswap, Gemini, and the Government of El Salvador. We’ve raised $26m from top investors including Point Nine, 1kx, Tim Draper, and Ledger Cathay.\n\nLocation: New York City\n\nThe role\n\nCryptio is hiring a Head of Lending to lead our Loan Management System (LMS) and build our emerging Digital Credit Network.\n\nThis is a senior, high-impact role at the intersection of institutional credit, financial infrastructure, and digital assets. You will own the strategy, product direction, and commercial success of our lending vertical; shaping how financial institutions and crypto enterprises manage collateralised lending, structured credit, and digital asset financing.\n\nYou will work cross-functionally across Product, Engineering, and Revenue, while engaging directly with senior leaders at financial institutions and crypto-native firms.\n\nWhat you'll do\n\n - Own the vision, roadmap, and commercial performance of Cryptio’s Loan Management System\n\n - Define high-value institutional lending use cases across crypto-backed loans, margin financing, structured credit, and treasury financing\n\n - Partner closely with Product and Engineering to design institutional-grade credit infrastructure with strong controls and scalability\n\n - Act as Cryptio’s senior subject-matter expert on credit and lending in enterprise sales cycles and executive conversations\n\n - Build relationships with lenders, custodians, asset managers, prime brokers, and credit funds\n\n - Contribute to the design and launch of Cryptio’s Digital Credit Network, including risk frameworks and participation models\n\n - Embed strong credit and risk thinking into product design, including collateral management, LTVs, lifecycle events, and reporting\n\n - Represent Cryptio externally in conversations around institutional digital asset lending\n\nWhy you’ll love this role\n\n - Own one of Cryptio’s most strategic growth initiatives\n\n - Build infrastructure at the core of institutional digital asset credit markets\n\n - Work directly with top-tier financial institutions and crypto-native leaders\n\n - High ownership, high visibility, and meaningful equity upside\n\nWhat we’re looking for\n\n - 10+ years of experience in credit, lending, or capital markets (institutional lending, structured credit, prime brokerage, or balance-sheet financing)\n\n - Direct exposure to crypto lending or digital asset financing\n\n - Strong understanding of collateral mechanics, margining, credit risk, and institutional reporting\n\n - Comfortable operating between traditional finance standards and crypto-native innovation\n\n - Executive presence with the ability to engage senior stakeholders, risk teams, and regulators\n\n - Entrepreneurial mindset with the ability to build and scale a new vertical\n\nInterview process\n\n - Recruiter Screen - 45 min\n\n - Hiring Manager Interview - 60 min - CEO + CRO\n\n - Case Study Sendoff\n\n - Case Presentation - 90 min - CEO + CRO\n\n - Culture Interview - 45 min - VP People\n\nPerks\n\n👩‍💻 Remote or Hybrid working\n\n🏝️ 25 days paid holiday plus bank holidays\n\n🙌 One additional day of annual leave each year, up to 30 total days\n\n🎂 Your birth off\n\n🧘 Mental health resources, wellbeing programs, and professional coaching\n\n🫶 Family-friendly policies\n\n💪 Fitness and wellness budget\n\n💻 MacBook Pro\n\n🖥️ $200 home office setup budget\n\n🎓Training and development budget\n\n*** we have additional benefits depending on location\n\nIf this sounds like you, we would love to hear from you 🙌\n\nAt Cryptio, we move fast and take ownership of outcomes. We learn from failures, celebrate wins, and let humility, curiosity, and a passion for crypto guide how we work. If you value collaboration and want to build with purpose, you’ll feel right at home here.",
